Silent vigil held for slain Hinton mother, toddler outside Alberta courthouse: ‘We need change’
By
Karen Bartko	 &amp;
Morgan Black
Global News
Posted September 21, 2021 2:26 pm
Updated September 22, 2021 2:03 pm
2:09
Silent vigil held for slain Hinton mother, toddler outside Alberta courthouse
Friends and family of 24-year-old Mchale Busch and her 16-month-old son Noah McConnell, the mother and child killed in Hinton last week, gathered at the Edson courthouse for a silent vigil Tuesday as the accused in their deaths was set to make a court appearance.  – Sep 21, 2021
